                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Denby</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Bayard</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1888-10-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">October</hi> 20, 1888</date>. (Received November
                        30.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 738.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I inclose herewith an estimate of the population
                    of China, prepared by the imperial maritime customs. It is based on the census
                    of 1879 and 1882.</p>
                <p>Official censuses in China are not entirely accurate.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Charles Denby.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <pb facs="0197" n="79" xml:id="pg_79"/>
                <frus:attachment>
